SIMPLE: explosive
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Explosive
<hw>Ex*plo"sive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>explosif</ets>.]</ety> <def>Driving or bursting out with violence
and noise; causing explosion; <as>as, the <ex>explosive</ex> force of
gunpowder</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Explosive</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Explosive
<hw>Ex*plo"sive</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An explosive agent;
a compound or mixture susceptible of a rapid chemical reaction, as
<stype>gunpowder</stype>, <stype>TNT</stype>, <stype>dynamite</stype>,
or <stype>nitro-glycerine</stype>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A sound produced by an explosive impulse of the
breath; <fld>(Phonetics)</fld> one of consonants <xex>p</xex>,
<xex>b</xex>, <xex>t</xex>, <xex>d</xex>, <xex>k</xex>, <xex>g</xex>,
which are sounded with a sort of explosive power of voice. <note>[See
<xex>Guide to Pronunciation</xex>, ⟦root⟧ 155-7, 184.]</note></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Explosively</ent>⟦br⟧
